<br>
1.  Already having all the plane gear:  This will never be true of FoR.  We have waves of people becoming planeable, currently planeable and obtaining gear, and retiring already having obtain plane gear.  Things just sort of evolved this way with us being a large alliance rather than a single guild.  This is probably one thing that FoR is different on from KEG, CIW, and BOTS.<br>
<br>
2.  FoR reserving a plane for two days.  Well, our current estimate for planeable FoR toons is about 100 to 120 ppl.  While FoR may be in a plane for two days, most of the people will be different on the two days.  While we will have some core people make both raids, may others will not get to go both days but have to rotate out.  So in any one raid signup, we have some necessary people who go both days, some who get to go one day but not the other, and then we still have some that don't get to go at all.<br>
<br>
Now on the BB guild/alliance quailification, I feel like others here that clearing isle 6 including the boss and obtaining the keys to move on to isle 7 should be the requirement.  Those who have been there and done it know that isle 6 is quite a bit harder than isle 5.  </font><P>Xantarran {Black Talons}, 
