<br>
Don't think others won't clear island 6.  It is a goal of our next Air raid to be sure.  I am sure others have the same goal.<br>
<br>
Everyone agrees to the proposed plan except the 2 day rule.  I just see it as being a problem in the making and would rather see it left out.  If there were less entities posting then it wouldn't be as big a problem.  But if we have 30 entities posting there just is no room to allow a few guilds/alliances to post 2 days.<br>
<br>
I think we need to push an agreement through and work on getting the calendar back in order.  Take off the 2 day rule(even though I feel our guild would benefit from it soon) and lets try and be fair to everyone out there.  The BB guilds will have more shots at gods without having to post 2 days in the planes.<br>
<br>
The problem is this!!  Focus right here on these 2 paragraphs.  Everyone is crying out to get more plane dates SOONER.  When we get more and more BB's then that SOONER becomes terms more suited for geological clocks.  And you CANNOT keep pushing the bar up to suit your Gdamn needs.  If you agree to this NOW, you can't say, &quot;oh wait too many big brothers lets push the bar up again so only guilds who can kill Trakanon will be big brothers.&quot;<br>
<br>
Fact is when more big brothers come on the scene with 2 day postings then we are back to square one.  Lets have some vision please.  You got the epic quest calendar, you have the chance at your epic quest items more often.  Lets go with that idea and run with it.<br>
<br>
I hope everyone can understand this,<br>
<br>
-Jairn</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uaxterixenobelix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Axterix EnObelix</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Toede</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>4</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>11/3/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>2:09:57 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Proposal Questions</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">My problem, like most others, is the 2 day postings allowed for the Big Brothers.<br>
<br>
Originally, we all could have 2 days and it was dropped to just a single day because there were just too many guilds.  I can see it returning to this state relatively quickly.<br>
<br>
In addition, for BotS, KEG, and Icewind, the additional day pretty much becomes a twink-fest.  Most of the mains have their gear and so much of the loot will go to secondaries, people that joined the guild just to get loot, or guests.  The main reason these guilds will want to book 2 days?  Epic quest loot.  But the Big Brother provisions are already there to get them more of that.  There really is no reason for double booking.  Especially when you consider that KEG is at what, 50 members?  10 over the limit to sign up.  That's it.  Just because they can handle the 5th island in Sky doesn't justify giving them an extra planar day when the majority of their own people already have planar gear.  Now, don't get me wrong, I know that KEG will invite people along, things won't rot, etc.  But it's the principle of the thing.  There is no justification for a guild that qualifies as Big Brother to get two days in fear or hate.<br>
<br>
Combine this with other guilds achieving big brother status (and my guess is that within a month or two, you'll have 2 or 3 more big brothers), we'll quickly end up with a situation which we just recently left.  Raising the bar isn't right either.  Either you are good enough to be a Big Brother now under the current standards or you aren't.  If the plan is to eventually up it to be that you must have killed Trakanon, visited isle 7, and killed VS... then that is the level the bar should be set at now.  From the beginning.  And if that means that Icewind, RoF, and KEG (hmmm, has BotS killed VS yet?) don't qualify right away, then so be it.  They might eventually, but the standards which judge their admittance should be the same as anyone else's.  Plan long term, don't plan for short term to fulfill your own greedy desires.  <br>
<br>
If it's a problem that there will be lots of big brothers later, then the only problem that exists is that the big brothers get too much.  After all, the goal of the Big Brother program is to ensure that epic quest mobs don't go to waste, right?  As long as that goal is met, to change it for any other reason would seem to indicate that it exists to feed the greed of certain guilds.<br>
<br>
I don't really care if you have tons of people becoming planar.  That's the price you pay for your size.  Again, you could form a new alliance of guilds that don't qualify for BB status with the exact same number of members and not qualify for 2 days... then neither should a BB.  If you want more planar days and have 150+ peeps, well, you can split and go your own way.  If it encourages a few people not to apply to a big guild because the line is too long to get loot, so much the better.  More people for the smaller/medium guilds, less people interested primarily in loot for the big boys.<br>
<br>
I'll support this proposal simply because it's better than chaos... but I'd like it much better without the 2 day crap... or at least, with only allowing BB's to schedule 3 days in hate/fear total, 2 in one, 1 in the other.  And I strongly advocate that whatever the conditions for joining the Big Brother club are, that they be set in stone, never to change, to keep it true to it's principles of max utilization and not pervert it to an institution established to feed the greed of a few.<br>
<br>
Axterix En'Obelix<br>
