<br>
***CIW, KEG, BOTS, and FOR propose the following...***<br>
<br>
I think we need to have more representation out there. =)<br>
<br>
<br>
***Revamp the posting entities. Atleast 40 planeable toons per entity, <br>
whether it be by guild or by alliance.***<br>
<br>
While, I think 40 at any plane raid is a bit much, but I am willing to accept this idea.  Heck, we have 71 planeable toons already.  I kind of think 30 is a more reasonable number.<br>
<br>
***Abolishment of the 2/3 rule.***<br>
<br>
Sure thing.<br>
<br>
*** If an entity has the 40 planeable toons, <br>
they invite who they please with a maximum of 6 people from any one guild.***<br>
<br>
No, I don't agree.  I know it sounds fair on paper, but it is too controlling.  I would say that if the number of invites equalled or exceeded the number of actual guild members there, then we would have issues, but 6 is too nit picky.  OMG I have 7 invites!?!?  You see what I mean?  I think it's too low, and there's no justification as to why only 6.  What if GuildA brough 40 of their guild to the planes, is  7 invites even close to abusing the system?  This does not make sense.  I would say if the invites exceed 40% of the current population in the plane, then that would be abuse.  Easier to set it at a percentage than any static number. =)<br>
<br>
***If there continues to be abuse of this calendar it will be brought up for public review with possible actions taken against the abuser.***<br>
<br>
I like that...gets the community involved.<br>
<br>
<br>
***Plane of Fear/Hate:***<br>
<br>
***KEG, FOR, CIW, BOTS be allowed to post 2 days per plane either <br>
consecutive or non-consecutive assuming those days are available vrs the number of posting entities.<br>
Other entities be allowed to post 1 day per plane.***<br>
<br>
This is wrong.  The issue we have all be fighting for is not extra concessions, whether they would ever exist or not, it's for EQUAL rights to the planes, and no waste.  This rule does not cover either base.  Fear and Hate are one day raids to all, regardless, the epic calendar can take of those who need to help the smaller guilds kill Inny or what not.  <br>
<br>
****Its our goal here to be able to get 2 days per plane a month for <br>
KEG, FOR, CIW, BOTS and 1 day per plane a month for other entities.<br>
This will vary depending on how many entities we get after it gets revamped.<br>
It could work out to more than that per month, or it could work out a <br>
little less.***<br>
<br>
It is my goal to keep things fair for all guilds, and this does not work.  Sorry, but your main argument has been waste and abuses to the system.  This is an abuse, and does not provide the solution to your problem with waste in the planes, in fact, considering you have stated that most of your members are full planes gear, this actually causes waste.  Oh yeah, invite rule, hehe, didn't you suggest only 6 invites?  ACK, a contradiction.  What if none of the 6 invites needed a plane item that dropped.  Waste.<br>
<br>
***Plane of Sky<br>
In order to maximize weekend enjoyment of the plane of sky, we propose<br>
the following:<br>
FRI/SAT postings<br>
SAT/SUN postings<br>
Meaning, if you have fri/sat reserved, you are entitled to islands 1 - 4 on friday,<br>
with saturday giving you islands 5+.<br>
The next guild that has sat/sun reserved will be entitled to islands 1 - 4 on saturday and 5+ on sunday, and so on.***<br>
<br>
Question, on this one.  Who is entitled to the fri/sat sat/sun postings?  Just need a clarification before I see a reason to agree.  RoS has been to Sky once, we started late, and went to 4 before we got pooped.  I am more than sure we will get to 5 and beyond soon enough, so I worry less about your &quot;qualifications&quot;, but I do want to know this more for the other guilds that want to experience Sky.<br>
<br>
<br>
***Big Brother***<br>
<br>
Probably needs rewording hehe, it's got an ominous tone to it, hehe.<br>
<br>
***Rotation Schedule between KEG, CIW, FOR, BOTS<br>
For the guilds who know they cannot kill Cazic/Innoruuk/Maestro,<br>
KEG, FOR, CIW, BOTS will be on call to assist in killing these mobs<br>
in exchange for the epic quest items. This is by invite only.****<br>
<br>
Fine by me, I think this was one of the major concessions we were willing to give.  Beyond that, no.  <br>
<br>
****If any guild knows they cannot complete epic quests, and agree that <br>
those items sitting in a bank rotting a way is a waste. It would be <br>
greatly appreciated if they would also use the big brother rotation<br>
schedule to have them loot the epic quest item.Your choice.****<br>
<br>
Fair enough.<br>
<br>
***Once a guild has cleared to Island 6 in sky(Bzzt island), they will be <br>
added to the list in this rotation assuming they choose to do so.<br>
**<br>
<br>
Fair enough as well.<br>
<br>
***All other calendar rules will remain the same and be eligible to change in the future due to the circumstances. those rules proposed to be changed will be discussed in an adult manner AT that time.***<br>
<br>
Eligible for future change by whom?<br>
<br>
***IF you are in agreement to this proposal and we can carry this forward and get the calendar up and running again please state your guild below if you are an authorized representative of your guild.***<br>
<br>
While I am not THE representative of my guild to approve or disapprove, I am going to have to say that ME, Siffu does not approve, although it does look like many of us officers are feeling the same way.<br>
<br>
I think it revolves around the concessions being made.  While, we were all willing to agree to the Epic quest concession to eliminate waste, we were never in favor of any guild getting extra days.  Oh, Yes, I am fully aware of the stated IF clause, but it goes against the spirit of the calendar.  Truth be known, there will be no IF.  There are too many people to have &quot;extra days&quot; given to anyone.  <br>
<br>
Lets infringe on others raids by allowing for the epic quest calendar, but lets begone with the &quot;extra day&quot; rubbish, bad idea.  I really don't want arguments about IF there is a day, as stated above, it's the principle behind the matter, and it has already got many, whose nerves are already rattled, feeling itchy trigger fingers again.  Lets keep it fair, just fair.<br>
<br>
Oh and Qwai, you will have to forgive me for not approving of it right away.  I like to read things and understand them before I sign my life away, am I the only one? =P  <br>
