</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umarcys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Marcys</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Toede</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>48</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>11/5/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>1:12:07 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/marky_harlock/images/smmarcys.jpg WIDTH=160 HEIGHT=125></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Proposal Questions</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">&gt;&gt;You require 40 planable members to post on Calendar.<br>
The guilds that have 40+ planable members are the ones that can kill the Gods - or think they can.<br>
They will never call in a &quot;Big Brother&quot; guild...<br>
<br>
By raising the number to 40, you eliminate the smaller guilds and alliances that are the most likely to call in a Big Brother guild. By pushing the bar higher to 40 planable toons, you will virtually eliminiate any chance of being called in for a God.&lt;&lt;<br>
<br>
<br>
That doesnt matter, because then there will be more posting days to go around....<br>
<br>
And i still would wager, some of the newer ppl to the planes, would still need help.<br>
<br>
