</table><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uscytheeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ScytheEQ</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Toede</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>1</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>11/5/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>1:52:28 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Proposal Questions</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">This proposal makes absolutely no sense.  First of all, stop trying to name certain entities and set them apart from others based on name/reputation alone.  The past is the past.  If you want to propose a set criteria, then lots of guilds are going to meet it in very short order, not just four.  There are probably another half-dozen guilds of a size that is larger than one or more of the &quot;Big Brothers&quot; proposed in terms of planes level characters.  What are you going to propose when they all proceed to clear Island 5/6/whatever within a month of this going out? <br>
<br>
Yep, some of the 4 guilds mentioned helped &quot;bust&quot; the planes.  That was over a year ago.  Get over it.  A simple matter of time and trial-and-error tactics.  The guilds with people who (a) had lots of free time to devote, and (b) had a drive to do things first and/or get all the loot first naturally did these things first.  This in no way means that any number of other guilds and players could not have done the same thing over time.  Adding just one of the largest of these up-and-coming guilds to your list does not solve anything, although it has silenced that particular guild's calls for fairness, which is pretty sad.<br>
<br>
The situation on The Rathe now is one of several large guilds trying to hold on to what they enjoyed in the past, while a slew of guilds inevitably catches up to them.  There will be 20+ guilds capable of doing some or all of these quests by Xmas.  Get used to it, and quit trying to eke out that last little elite spot for yourselves.  This is a game after all, and you're making yourselves and all us arguing over these &quot;precious resources&quot; look pretty silly.  It's even funnier since Velious will be out in 2 months and you'll all be fighting over whichever uber-loot zone is identified first, just like you did for Kunark.<br>
<br>
The proposals that do not make any special allowances for any particular named guild, but only make allowances based on proven guild size or measurable capabilities are the right ones.  Take your names out of it and let's get back to playing.</font><P><P><i><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uscytheeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ScytheEQ</A> at: 11/5/00 1:53:17 pm</FONT><br></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufoladen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>foladen</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Toede</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>59</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>11/5/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>2:42:33 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">some inflection from this side.</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Allow to me inject some thinking from both viewpoints. On one side, from a guild that has been posting planes raids for only 3 or 4 months so i understand the frustration of the smaller guilds and on the other hand from one of the larger guilds on the server.<br>
<br>
The 40 toon rule should pass for now. Its simply a matter of logistics people. The rathe is overpopulated with hi lvls. This gives room for more posting dates. Concessions need to be made for now. Once velious is out and those 2 planes are active then we can discuss it again. But right now i vote yes for this.<br>
<br>
After much thought and consideration on the 2 day rule I vote no. the idea of unclaimed days going for training of those unguilded or needing help would be wonderful, but already by a few posts i see i know that some will not do that but instead just keep it for a 2nd planes day for themselves. there is just too much room for abuse there. <br>
Im not saying all will abuse this, so please dont get me wrong but when i read posts arguing for it saying we deserve more from the context of the posts....well that puts up a big red light. To those who wish to really use the day for what KEG is proposing i apologize but i cannot vote for this at this time. No one deserves special treatment. If set rules preventing the abuse of this suggested 2nd day can be posted and abusers lose right to 2nd day i will gladly vote yes. <br>
<br>
The isle 6 clear to be big brother guild i agree to.<br>
